de.oaam.model.oaam.restrictions

Interface SegregationRestriction

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ModeDependentElementA, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA, VariantDependentElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SegregationRestrictionImpl

    public interface SegregationRestriction
extends OaamBaseElementA, ModeDependentElementA, VariantDependentElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Segregation Restriction'. Functions and signals can be defined to be segregated. This implies that they have to be mapped to different devices or connections. In the segregation two groups A and B are defined. Elements in group A must be segregated from elements in group B.

    The following features are supported:

    • Tasks A
    • Tasks B
    • Dissimilar Technology
    • Dissimilar Location
    • Subfunctions A
    • Subfunctions B
    • Dissimilar Area
    • Dissimilar Power Source
    • Signals A
    • Signals B
    • Task Groups A
    • Task Groups B
    • Signal Groups B
    • Signal Groups A
    • Devices A
    • Devices B
    • Connections A
    • Connections B
    See Also:
    RestrictionsPackage.getSegregationRestriction()
